    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.22-23_0001"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        St. Louis.
                        April 19. 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Having so recently suffered the loss of my own wife, I am aware of the futility of condolences. Yet I was heartened by notes from friends of ours.</p>
                
                <p>I had high regard for Mrs. Neihardt, as I have for you. I know the void that is left
                
                <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.22-23_0002"/>
                    
                <fw type="authorial">- 2 -</fw>
                
                    and I do not want the occassion to pass without reiterating my feeling of regard and expressing my hope that all is for the ultimate &#8212; if totally obscure &#8212; best.</p>
                
                <p>My sympathy, sir, and friendship.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Leighton Rutledge</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
